###Block: General Feats
# Feat Name				Type			Req. Att.	Required Feat					Required Non-Monster Lvl	Maximum Size	Required Skill		Required Stat	Required Text											Description																					Source Page
Cling Attack
	TYPE:Combat
	PRESIZELTEQ:T
	DESC:You attach yourself to larger enemies allowing you to attack up close and personal.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.11
	BENEFIT:If you share the space of a creature Medium-sized or larger, you can make a special Combat Maneuver check with a +8 bonus to hold onto the surface of the creature. Once attached you lose any Dexterity bonus to your AC, as does your opponent against your attacks. It takes a move action to maintain the hold, but you can still use standard actions normally. You must succeed on a concentration check to cast a spell or use a spell-like ability while clinging. Opponents can only attack you with one-handed weapons or attempt to remove you with a grapple. You receive a +8 bonus to your Combat Maneuver Defense against the grapple check.

Companion Aid
	TYPE:General
	DESC:Your companion creature helps you more than is typical.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:When flanking or aiding another, your animal companion or familiar grants you a +4 bonus.

Companion Friend
	TYPE:General
	DESC:You've become adept at working with willful companions.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:You get a +4 bonus to Diplomacy or Intimidate checks to convince a willful companion to do something it does not want to do.

Drake Dart
	TYPE:Combat
	PREFEAT:1,Dodge
	PRESKILL:1,Acrobatics=2
	DESC:By imitating a drake's quickness, you give yourself a better chance to avoid attacks of opportunity provoked by movement.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:In place of your armor class, you may make an Acrobatics check to set the DC for an attack of opportunity against you.

Ease of Form
	TYPE:General
	PRETEXT:Ability to shapechange into two different types of creatures.
	MULT:YES
	CHOOSE:USERINPUT|TITLE=Creature Form
	SELECT:1
	DESC:You are comfortable changing shape into a favorite creature.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:When changing into your creature shapes, treat the duration as if modified by the Extend Spell feat. This includes any change to spell level and other variables. This feat may be chosen multiple times. Each time it is chosen, it applies to a different form. The benefits of this feat do not stack with Extend Spell.

Exceptional Relationship
	TYPE:General
	PREFEAT:1,Willful Companion Drake
	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=11
	PRESTAT:1,CHA=15
	DESC:You and your drake companion share a stronger bond.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:Your drake companion can serve as an animal companion or improved familiar if you have access to those abilities. While you still must spend 1 gp per HD per day on your companion drake, you no longer need to make Diplomacy checks as the two of you have built a bond of trust.

Foe Climb
	TYPE:Combat
	PREFEAT:3,Cling Attack,Dodge,Mobility
	PRESIZELTEQ:T
	DESC:You can scale larger opponents.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:When you make a successful Cling Attack against a Medium or larger opponent, you retain your Dexterity bonus to AC and you need not spend a move action to maintain your grip, allowing you to use full-round actions.

Shared Companion
	TYPE:Teamwork
	PRETEXT:At least one character must have a companion creature or familiar
	DESC:You treat another character's companion as if it were your own.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:If you and another character have this feat, you gain benefits related to the other character's animal companion or familiar. The other character's familiar grants you the same bonus, reduced by 1, as it grants its master. If the other character has an animal companion, you may use one trick the animal has learned (specified when a character first takes this feat or when another character gains an animal companion) as if you were its master. This feat grants you a +4 circumstance bonus to use other tricks the animal knows.

Tooth and Claw Form
	TYPE:Combat
	PREATT:1
	PREFEAT:1,Improved Unarmed Strike
	DESC:Striking with speed and grace, you fight like a dragon.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12
	BENEFIT:As a swift action, you can choose to make your unarmed attacks deal bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage. This lasts for one hour or until you change the effect with a swift action.

Willful Companion Drake
	TYPE:General
	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=5
	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13
	DEFINE:WillfulCompanionDrakeHDMax|0
	DESC:You gain a companion drake, though it doesn't regard you as its master.
	SOURCEPAGE:pg.13
	BENEFIT:You attract a drake with no higher than %1HD as your companion. The creature has a starting attitude of Helpful. (See special)|WillfulCompanionDrakeHDMax
